{"type":"message","id":"17fcff37","parentId":"68602501","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:17.157Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-23 20:39 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Add a real-time chat feature for Dean ONLY (dean's agent ID is \"main\") to the existing Mission Control React app at /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/.\n\n**What to build:**\nTransform Dean's MessageModal into a full chat interface.\n\n**Files to modify:**\n- `src/components/MessageModal.tsx` — rebuild as a chat window with:\n  - Scrollable message history loaded from gateway\n  - Text input at bottom + send button\n  - Messages displayed as chat bubbles (user on right in blue/indigo, Dean on left in gray/frosted glass)\n  - Auto-scroll to bottom on new messages\n  - Loading indicator while Dean \"thinks\"\n  - Timestamps on each message\n  \n- `src/lib/gateway.ts` — add these functions:\n  - `getChatHistory(agentId)` — uses gateway sessions_list to find the session, then reads transcript from `transcriptPath` (session transcript JSONL file on disk)\n  - `sendChatMessage(agentId, message, sessionKey)` — uses gateway sessions_send tool to send message to the agent's session and get a real response\n  \n- `src/hooks/useAgentStatus.ts` — already fine, may need minor updates\n\n**CRITICAL - Gateway API:**\n- Gateway at http://localhost:18789 via Vite proxy /tools\n- Auth: Bearer token 286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111\n- For sessions_send tool: POST /tools/invoke with tool=\"sessions_send\", args={sessionKey, message}\n- Response format: {ok: true, result: {response: \"Dean response text...\"}} or similar\n- For transcript: read the transcriptPath file from the session (gateway can serve files or we need to use a different tool)\n\n**IMPORTANT - Session key for Dean:**\n- Dean uses agentId \"main\", his direct session key: \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444\"\n- His latest sessionId: \"f23d1627-493c-4e87-80b1-73fc2cca0250\"\n\n**Styling:**\n- Keep the iOS 26 frosted glass aesthetic\n- Chat bubbles: user messages = indigo gradient bg with white text, right-aligned\n- Dean messages = frosted glass bg (bg-white/5), left-aligned, with 🤖 emoji prefix\n- Input bar at bottom: frosted glass, rounded, send button on right\n- Make it feel like iMessages — clean, minimal, elegant\n\n**Wire it up:**\n1. MessageModal.tsx imports sendChatMessage from gateway.ts\n2. When Bobby hits send, call sendChatMessage(\"main\", message, \"agent:main:telegram:direct:8212808444\")\n3. Show typing indicator while waiting\n4. Append Dean's response to the chat history\n5. Store chat history in React state (in-memory, doesn't need to persist)\n\n**For the other 7 agents (emmy, x, finn, yoyos, rex, dj, cody):** For now, just make their modals show a message \"Chat coming soon for [agent name]\" instead of the chat interface. We're only building real chat for Dean first.\n\n**Run npm run build when done to compile.**\n\nMake it polished — this is a core feature. Chat should feel smooth and responsive."}],"timestamp":1774312757155}}
{"type":"message","id":"147c0c58","parentId":"17fcff37","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:21.353Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me start by reading the existing files to understand the current structure of the Mission Control React app.","thinkingSignature":"04454e866ac89b117ed74048385228253e91afd836d1607c062de094ae60928d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gjwb5ijwy4a0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/lib/gateway.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gjwb5ijwy4a0_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/components/MessageModal.tsx"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gjwb5ijwy4a0_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/hooks/useAgentStatus.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":133,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17074,"totalTokens":17261,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0001596,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.0064027500000000005,"total":0.006578550000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774312757157,"responseId":"06111035690dbfb89853a218b88086c9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"86afd8b5","parentId":"147c0c58","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:21.386Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gjwb5ijwy4a0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const GATEWAY_BASE = '/tools';\n\nexport interface GatewayResponse<T> {\n  ok: boolean;\n  result: T;\n}\n\nexport interface SessionsListResult {\n  content: Array<{ type: string; text: string }>;\n  details: {\n    count: number;\n    sessions: Array<{\n      key: string;\n      updatedAt: number;\n      status: string;\n      endedAt: number | null;\n    }>;\n  };\n}\n\nexport async function listSessions(): Promise<SessionsListResult> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${GATEWAY_BASE}/invoke`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ tool: 'sessions_list', args: {} }),\n  });\n\n  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Gateway error: ${res.status}`);\n  const data: GatewayResponse<SessionsListResult> = await res.json();\n  if (!data.ok) throw new Error('Gateway returned not-ok');\n  return data.result;\n}\n\nexport async function sendMessage(message: string): Promise<void> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${GATEWAY_BASE}/invoke`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      tool: 'message',\n      args: {\n        action: 'send',\n        channel: 'telegram',\n        target: '8212808444',\n        message,\n      },\n    }),\n  });\n\n  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Gateway error: ${res.status}`);\n  const data = await res.json();\n  if (!data.ok) throw new Error('Gateway returned not-ok');\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312761382}}
{"type":"message","id":"61aebd72","parentId":"86afd8b5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:21.389Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gjwb5ijwy4a0_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type { Agent } from '../types';\nimport { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react';\n\ninterface MessageModalProps {\n  agent: Agent | null;\n  onClose: () => void;\n  onSend: (message: string) => Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport const MessageModal = ({ agent, onClose, onSend }: MessageModalProps) => {\n  const [message, setMessage] = useState('');\n  const [sending, setSending] = useState(false);\n  const textareaRef = useRef<HTMLTextAreaElement>(null);\n\n  const handleSend = async () => {\n    if (!message.trim() || sending) return;\n    setSending(true);\n    try {\n      await onSend(message.trim());\n      setMessage('');\n      onClose();\n    } catch {\n      setSending(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (agent && textareaRef.current) {\n      textareaRef.current.focus();\n    }\n  }, [agent]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {\n      if (e.key === 'Escape') onClose();\n      if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === 'Enter') handleSend();\n    };\n    window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);\n    return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);\n  }, [message, sending, onClose]);\n\n  if (!agent) return null;\n\n  return (\n    <div\n      className=\"fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4\"\n      onClick={(e) => e.target === e.currentTarget && onClose()}\n    >\n      {/* Backdrop */}\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm\" />\n\n      {/* Modal */}\n      <div\n        className=\"\n          relative w-full max-w-md\n          backdrop-blur-xl bg-white/[0.06] border border-white/15 rounded-2xl\n          shadow-[0_25px_50px_rgba(0,0,0,0.6),0_0_80px_rgba(129,140,248,0.1)]\n          flex flex-col gap-5 p-7\n        \"\n        style={{ animation: 'fadeIn 0.2s ease-out' }}\n      >\n        {/* Header */}\n        <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between\">\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3\">\n            <span className=\"text-3xl\">{agent.emoji}</span>\n            <div>\n              <h2 className=\"text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100\">{agent.name}</h2>\n              <p className=\"text-xs text-slate-400\">{agent.role}</p>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          <button\n            onClick={onClose}\n            className=\"w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-200 transition-colors\"\n            aria-label=\"Close\"\n          >\n            ✕\n          </button>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Divider */}\n        <div className=\"h-px bg-white/10\" />\n\n        {/* Textarea */}\n        <textarea\n          ref={textareaRef}\n          value={message}\n          onChange={e => setMessage(e.target.value)}\n          placeholder={`Message ${agent.name} via Telegram...`}\n          rows={4}\n          className=\"\n            w-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-4\n            text-slate-200 placeholder-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed\n            resize-none outline-none\n            focus:border-accent-indigo/50 focus:bg-white/[0.07]\n            transition-colors\n          \"\n        />\n\n        {/* Hint */}\n        <p className=\"text-xs text-slate-500 -mt-2\">\n          Press{' '}\n          <kbd className=\"px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-white/10 text-slate-400 font-mono text-[10px]\">⌘</kbd>{' '}\n          +{' '}\n          <kbd className=\"px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-white/10 text-slate-400 font-mono text-[10px]\">Enter</kbd>{' '}\n          to send\n        </p>\n\n        {/* Send button */}\n        <button\n          onClick={handleSend}\n          disabled={!message.trim() || sending}\n          className=\"\n            w-full py-3.5 rounded-xl font-semibold text-sm\n            bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-indigo to-accent-violet\n            text-white shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(129,140,248,0.4)]\n            hover:shadow-[0_4px_30px_rgba(129,140,248,0.6)]\n            disabled:opacity-40 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:shadow-none\n            transition-all duration-200\n          \"\n        >\n          {sending ? 'Sending...' : 'Send via Telegram'}\n        </button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n};\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312761386}}
{"type":"message","id":"b69d1fed","parentId":"61aebd72","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:21.409Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gjwb5ijwy4a0_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import type { Session, AgentState, ConnectionState } from '../types';\nimport { useState, useEffect, useCallback, useRef } from 'react';\nimport { listSessions } from '../lib/gateway';\nimport { AGENTS } from '../types';\n\nfunction deriveAgentStatus(session: Session | null): AgentState {\n  if (!session) return { status: 'offline', lastActive: null, session: null };\n  if (session.status === 'failed') return { status: 'error', lastActive: session.updatedAt, session };\n  // Only busy if running AND recently updated (within 5 min) — avoids stuck stale sessions\n  if ((session.status === 'running' || session.status === 'active') && Date.now() - session.updatedAt < 5 * 60_000) {\n    return { status: 'busy', lastActive: session.updatedAt, session };\n  }\n  if (Date.now() - session.updatedAt < 30_000) return { status: 'online', lastActive: session.updatedAt, session };\n  return { status: 'offline', lastActive: session.updatedAt, session };\n}\n\nfunction findSessionForAgent(sessions: Session[]): (prefixes: string[]) => Session | null {\n  return (prefixes: string[]) => {\n    return sessions.find(s => prefixes.some(p => s.key.startsWith(p))) ?? null;\n  };\n}\n\nexport function useAgentStatus(pollIntervalMs = 3000) {\n  const [agentStates, setAgentStates] = useState<Record<string, AgentState>>(() =>\n    Object.fromEntries(AGENTS.map(a => [a.id, { status: 'offline', lastActive: null, session: null }]))\n  );\n  const [connectionState, setConnectionState] = useState<ConnectionState>('disconnected');\n  const [initialized, setInitialized] = useState(false);\n  const pollTimerRef = useRef<ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchSessions = useCallback(async () => {\n    setConnectionState('polling');\n    try {\n      const result = await listSessions();\n      const rawSessions = result.details.sessions;\n\n      const sessions: Session[] = rawSessions.map(s => ({\n        key: s.key,\n        updatedAt: s.updatedAt,\n        status: s.status as Session['status'],\n        endedAt: s.endedAt,\n      }));\n\n      const findSession = findSessionForAgent(sessions);\n\n      setAgentStates(\n        Object.fromEntries(\n          AGENTS.map(agent => [agent.id, deriveAgentStatus(findSession(agent.sessionPrefixes))])\n        )\n      );\n      setConnectionState('connected');\n      if (!initialized) setInitialized(true);\n    } catch {\n      setConnectionState('disconnected');\n    }\n  }, [initialized]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetchSessions();\n    pollTimerRef.current = setInterval(fetchSessions, pollIntervalMs);\n    return () => {\n      if (pollTimerRef.current) clearInterval(pollTimerRef.current);\n    };\n  }, [fetchSessions, pollIntervalMs]);\n\n  return { agentStates, connectionState, initialized };\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312761389}}
{"type":"message","id":"5318ba5e","parentId":"b69d1fed","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:26.310Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the existing code. Let me also look at the types and other relevant files to understand the full structure.","thinkingSignature":"4fd793e4917a8d502b0567c57e614a4978ac481f99728001415deef98d580bfb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v84mx1hvpw38_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/types/index.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v84mx1hvpw38_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/tailwind.config.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3090,"output":102,"cacheRead":16299,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19491,"cost":{"input":0.000927,"output":0.0001224,"cacheRead":0.0009779399999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00202734}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774312761392,"responseId":"061110396aa67c2d1781ae1fe3ec9ba3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e4b4a42c","parentId":"5318ba5e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:26.330Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v84mx1hvpw38_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"export type AgentStatus = 'online' | 'busy' | 'offline' | 'error';\nexport type ConnectionState = 'connected' | 'polling' | 'disconnected';\n\nexport interface Session {\n  key: string;\n  updatedAt: number;\n  status: 'done' | 'running' | 'active' | 'failed';\n  endedAt: number | null;\n}\n\nexport interface Agent {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  role: string;\n  emoji: string;\n  sessionPrefixes: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface AgentState {\n  status: AgentStatus;\n  lastActive: number | null;\n  session: Session | null;\n}\n\nexport const AGENTS: Agent[] = [\n  { id: 'main',   name: 'Dean',   role: 'General Assistant',    emoji: '🤖', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:main:'] },\n  { id: 'emmy',   name: 'Emmy',   role: 'Email Specialist',      emoji: '🦋', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:emmy:'] },\n  { id: 'x',      name: 'X',      role: 'X/Twitter Specialist', emoji: '⚡', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:x:'] },\n  { id: 'finn',   name: 'Finn',   role: 'Finance Specialist',    emoji: '🧊', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:finn:'] },\n  { id: 'yoyos',  name: 'YoYo',   role: 'YouTube Specialist',    emoji: '🎥', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:yoyos:'] },\n  { id: 'rex',    name: 'Rex',    role: 'Research Executive',   emoji: '🔍', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:rex:'] },\n  { id: 'dj',     name: 'DJ',     role: 'Music Specialist',     emoji: '🎧', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:dj:'] },\n  { id: 'cody',   name: 'Cody',   role: 'Coding Expert',        emoji: '💻', sessionPrefixes: ['agent:cody:'] },\n];\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312766327}}
{"type":"message","id":"229841ca","parentId":"e4b4a42c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:39:26.335Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v84mx1hvpw38_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */\nexport default {\n  content: [\n    \"./index.html\",\n    \"./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}\",\n  ],\n  theme: {\n    extend: {\n      colors: {\n        void: '#08080e',\n        glass: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.05)',\n        'glass-border': 'rgba(255,255,255,0.10)',\n        'glass-border-active': 'rgba(255,255,255,0.20)',\n        accent: {\n          indigo: '#818cf8',\n          violet: '#a78bfa',\n          pink: '#f472b6',\n        },\n        status: {\n          online: '#34d399',\n          busy: '#a78bfa',\n          offline: '#6b7280',\n          error: '#f87171',\n        },\n      },\n      fontFamily: {\n        sans: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],\n        mono: ['JetBrains Mono', 'SF Mono', 'monospace'],\n      },\n      animation: {\n        'pulse-glow': 'pulse-glow 2s ease-in-out infinite',\n        'shimmer': 'shimmer 2s linear infinite',\n      },\n      keyframes: {\n        'pulse-glow': {\n          '0%, 100%': { opacity: '1', boxShadow: '0 0 8px 2px rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.6)' },\n          '50%': { opacity: '0.7', boxShadow: '0 0 16px 4px rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.9)' },\n        },\n        'shimmer': {\n          '0%': { backgroundPosition: '-200% 0' },\n          '100%': { backgroundPosition: '200% 0' },\n        },\n      },\n      backdropBlur: {\n        xl: '20px',\n      },\n    },\n  },\n  plugins: [],\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774312766331}}
